# ABENA Healthcare Blockchain - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
ABENA is a Substrate/Polkadot-based blockchain for healthcare. The stack includes:
- **Node**: abena-node (Substrate-based)
- **Runtime**: abena-runtime
- **Pallets**: patient-health-records, patient-identity, abena-coin, quantum-computing, and 15+ custom FRAME pallets

## Code Conventions
- Use Rust edition 2021
- Follow Substrate/Polkadot SDK patterns (polkadot-stable2512)
- Pallet configs use `Config` trait with associated types
- Prefer `#[pallet::call_index(N)]` for extrinsics

## Path Notes
- Project root has a space: `C:\Users\Jan Marie\Abena Blockchain`
- When running terminal commands, wrap paths in quotes: `cd "C:\Users\Jan Marie\Abena Blockchain"`
- On Windows, use PowerShell env var syntax: `$env:RUST_LOG='info'; cargo run ...`

## Build & Run
- Build node: `cargo build -p abena-node --release`
- Dev with temp chain: `cargo run -p abena-node -- --dev --tmp`
- On Linux/WSL, RocksDB and protoc are required: `apt install build-essential clang libclang-dev libssl-dev pkg-config cmake protobuf-compiler`

## File Structure
- `pallets/` - FRAME pallets
- `runtime/` - Runtime assembly
- `node/` - Node binary and CLI
- `services/fhir-api/` - FHIR API service
- `cli/` - Node.js CLI tools
- `connectors/` - EHR connectors

## AI Assistance
- Preserve Substrate/FRAME idioms when editing pallets
- When adding pallets, register in runtime and workspace Cargo.toml
- Healthcare data: follow HL7/FHIR conventions where relevant
